snippet.textDisplay: UK is a bit delayed. You’ve been able to get the bottled Big Mac sauce for at home from McDonald’s (or as us Australians call it- Maccas) for years now. Plus our grocery stores sell their own version of Big Mac sauce called “special burger sauce” which is like $3 and taste super super similar. Also in McDonald’s we were able to get little sauce tubs of Big Mac sauce for over 5-6 years at least, if not more as a dipping sauce. They don’t come already sealed like yours, they just fill them up from the Big Mac sauce bottle they use to put on your actual Big Mac into little sauce tubs that comes with a lid. (if that makes sense)

snippet.textDisplay: I've lived in Turkey for almost 13 years and it's a lovely country! If you want to go sightseeing I'd recommend you visit Istanbul, but if you want to have a more relaxed holiday I'd recommend Antalya, Fethiye and Kuşadası. Antalya and Fethiye can get quite hot in the summer (it can get upto 40°C) but they can also be quite loud. Kuşadası is a more calm place. Kuşadası also means Bird Island so you may see loads of birds in groups. 😊🇹🇷
